a test to check latency and bandwidth across
pcie in duplex mode communication.

Generates random double precision floating point 
numbers and sends them towards ml605 on riffa channels.
The receiving thread listens on loopbacked numbers.

Prints first 10 DWORDS sent and received for user to 
verify correct functioning of the example design; 
and transmission and reception speeds.

To check speed performance vs data size, number of words
can be changed in the cpp file by changing "numWords" variable.
"numWords" must be even in this case.
